It’s time to rise and end this suffocating situation in our nation.
Nepali people can no longer remain silent in the face of corruption, oppression, and the growing dictatorship. This is not the struggle of a single generation—it is the duty of all Nepalis.
No force, no intimidation, no abuse of power can suppress the voice of a united people. Our anger is stronger than their bullets, our courage greater than their threats.

Wake up, unite, and come to the streets. The time for silence is over—the time for action is now.
